:: LinksDemo [docs links]
!Links & Navigation Reference

A consolidated reference for every link form SugarCube supports.

!!Simple links (markup)
[[Time]]
[[Go to the Time passage|Time]]

!!Arrow separator forms
Right-arrow form: Go to Time->Time
Left-arrow form: Time<-Click here

!!Links with setters
[[Add 5 gold|Time][$playerGold += 5]]
[[Take a torch|Time][$inventory.pushUnique("Torch")]]

!!Image links
[img[images/icon.png][Time]]
[img[Tooltip text|images/icon.png][Time]]

!!HTML anchor with data-passage / data-setter
<a data-passage="Time" data-setter="$playerHP -= 5">Take damage and visit Time</a>

!!{{{<<link>>}}} — text-only (no navigation)
<<link "Click me — no navigation">>
        <<set $flags.clickedPlainLink to true>>
        <<replace "#plain-link-out">>Plain link clicked at <<= time()>>ms.<</replace>>
<</link>>
@@#plain-link-out;@@

!!{{{<<link>>}}} — with target passage
<<link "Visit Time via macro" "Time">><</link>>

!!{{{<<link>>}}} — with body (setter + target)
<<link "Take a potion and visit Time" "Time">>
        <<set $playerHP to Math.min($playerMaxHP, $playerHP + 20)>>
<</link>>

!!{{{<<link>>}}} — with image as label
<<link "[img[images/button.png]]" "Time">><</link>>

!!{{{<<link>>}}} — backtick expression arg
<<set _target to "Time">>
<<link `"Visit " + _target` _target>><</link>>

!!{{{<<button>>}}} — renders a {{{<button>}}} element
<<button "Plain button">>
        <<set $flags.clickedButton to true>>
        <<replace "#plain-btn-out">>Button clicked.<</replace>>
<</button>>
@@#plain-btn-out;@@

<<button "Button that navigates" "Time">><</button>>

!!{{{<<back>>}}} — undo history
<<back "Back one step">>
<<back [[Back to Time.|Time]]>>

!!{{{<<return>>}}} — forward to a previously visited passage
<<return>>
[[Return to start|Start]]

!!{{{<<goto>>}}} — immediate forward (no input)
/%
        NOTE: <<link>> wikifies its text argument. If the text contains literal
        <<macro>> syntax, those macros get invoked during wikification, which can
        produce restricted interactive elements (<button>, <a>, etc.) and throw
        "text content contains restricted elements". To show literal <<goto>> in
        a link label, use string concatenation with escaped angle brackets, or
        simply avoid <<>> in the label text.
%/
<<link "Trigger a goto immediately">>
        <<goto "Time">>
<</link>>

!!{{{<<actions>>}}} — deprecated v2.37.0 (one-shot link list)
<<actions "Time" "Start">>

!!{{{<<choice>>}}} — deprecated v2.37.0 (one-shot choice)
<<choice "Time" "Make a one-shot choice">>

!!Visited-link class (only when Config.addVisitedLinkClass = true)
Visit [[Time]] once, then look — it has the {{{.link-visited}}} class.

<<return "Return to start">>
